&lt;li&gt;💻 Latest MacBook Pro &amp;amp; tech accessories&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Whop&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whop is a financial technology company on a mission to provide the world with sustainable income. Our vision is to create the world’s largest internet market, where people can create, connect, and transact all from a single platform. Whop enables individuals and businesses to accept payments, launch ventures, and engage with others across the network.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today, Whop facilitates over $3 billion in annual payouts to people in 144 countries. Growth continues to accelerate, with gross transaction volume increasing roughly 25% month over month.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whop has raised hundreds of millions from institutional investors like Insight, Bain Capital Ventures, A*, and Peter Thiel, including a recent strategic investment from Tether, the largest stablecoin company in the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our current team is made up of young, passionate entrepreneurs who grew up on the internet — over 75% built a business before joining Whop, including 53 former founders and 30 who scaled past $1M in revenue. Product leadership includes backgrounds from Meta and Robinhood.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information, visit&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.whop.com/&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;whop.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Payments Partnerships Manager, you will support the day to day partner relationships management, execution, and optimization of Whop’s payments partner ecosystem.&amp;nbsp;You will work closely with leadership to manage day-to-day coordination with processors, fintech partners, and infrastructure providers. The focus is on execution, analysis, and relationship support — not leading negotiations independently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scope:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and grow relationships with key partners including banks, PSPs, networks, and BNPL providers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead onboarding and integrations with new partners, working closely with Product, Engineering, Risk, and Operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive performance across payment flows, focusing on conversion, cost, and reliability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and develop new partnership opportunities across the payments ecosystem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Negotiate agreements that support new products and scalable infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate partner and performance insights into product and business impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help shape the roadmap by identifying opportunities enabled through payments infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
