&lt;li&gt;Within 60 days, you are independently managing partner relationships and

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Whop&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whop is on a mission to deliver everyone a sustainable income. We&#39;re building the internet&#39;s leading commerce platform for digital products — empowering creators, communities, and entrepreneurs to monetize their knowledge, tools, and audiences. We move fast, operate with extreme ownership, and obsess over enabling our sellers to grow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Strategic Finance Lead to be a key partner to our executive team as we scale. This is a high-impact, high-visibility role sitting at the intersection of finance, strategy, and operations. You&#39;ll own the financial model, drive critical business decisions, and help shape the direction of the company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a back-office accounting role. We want someone who can translate complex financial data into clear strategic narratives, challenge assumptions, and operate as a genuine business partner to every team at Whop.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own the financial model.&lt;/strong&gt; Build and maintain a dynamic, company-wide model that supports scenario planning, fundraising, and long-range forecasting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive the operating cadence.&lt;/strong&gt; Lead monthly and quarterly business reviews, track KPIs across revenue, margins, and unit economics, and surface insights that drive action.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support fundraising and investor relations.&lt;/strong&gt; Prepare board materials, investor updates, and diligence packages; serve as a key point of contact for investors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build the finance function.&lt;/strong&gt; As an early member of the finance org, you&#39;ll help define processes, tooling, and team structure as we scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manage budgeting and headcount planning.&lt;/strong&gt; Partner with department heads to set budgets, manage spend, and make tough prioritization calls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analyze marketplace economics.&lt;/strong&gt; Develop deep intuition for Whop&#39;s platform metrics — GMV, take rate, seller LTV, cohort retention — and translate them into business insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5–8 years of experience in investment banking, growth equity, venture capital, or strategic finance at a high-growth tech company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptionally strong financial modeling skills — you can build a 3-statement model, LBO, or cohort analysis from scratch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to influence senior stakeholders with clear, data-driven storytelling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable operating in ambiguity; you don&#39;t need a playbook to get started&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with marketplace or SaaS business models is a strong plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative by nature — you build trust across functions and communicate with directness and clarity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scrappy, entrepreneurial mindset — excited to build systems and processes where none exist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The expected salary range for this position is $140,000 to $200,000 annually, with final compensation determined based on experience, skills, and qualifications.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;U.S. Indirect Tax Senior Manager &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Palo Alto, CA (U.S.) Hybrid&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Whop&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://whop.com/home-feed/&quot;&gt;Whop&lt;/a&gt; builds software for internet commerce. Our mission is to help people earn income online by giving creators, solopreneurs, communities, and internet-native businesses the tools to sell digital products, software, access, services, and memberships at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From paid communities and trading tools to SaaS products, educational content, and exclusive access, Whop supports a wide range of online businesses. We are product-focused, customer-oriented, and fast-moving. We focus on building reliable systems, hiring strong people, and supporting the entrepreneurs who rely on us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;We are seeking a Senior Manager, U.S. Indirect Tax to join our growing Tax Department and help scale our U.S. services and commerce platform. This role will lead sales and use tax strategy across product launches, business initiatives, compliance, audits, and tax operations, while partnering closely with Product, Engineering, Legal, Finance, and Operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role reports directly to the Director of Tax. As an early member of the tax team, you will play a critical role in shaping Whop’s approach to sales and use taxation across existing and emerging business models. You will evaluate complex digital commerce transactions, advise on marketplace facilitator and platform tax issues, support nexus and taxability analyses, and help build scalable processes and systems that support rapid growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position sits at the intersection of tax, technology, and operations, offering a unique opportunity to influence product design, automate tax processes, and establish best-in-class indirect tax practices within a high-growth technology company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On-site work at the Palo Alto office is currently required on Mondays, Tuesdays, and Thursdays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own U.S. sales and use tax compliance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead U.S. sales and use tax compliance across all applicable state and local jurisdictions, including manage nexus analyses, registrations, return filings, reconciliations, and compliance monitoring.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor legislative and regulatory developments and assess their impact on Whop&#39;s products, services, and operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Product Taxability Analysis&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate the sales and use tax treatment of new products, features, services, and business initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product, Engineering, and Legal teams throughout the product development lifecycle to ensure tax requirements are considered early and implemented effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Develop and Document Tax Positions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish, maintain, and periodically review formal sales and use tax position documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure tax positions remain aligned with evolving laws, regulations, and business models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support risk assessments and maintain defensible audit-ready documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Audits and Tax Controversy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage sales and use tax audits, notices, information requests, and voluntary disclosure initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with external advisors and state tax authorities to resolve matters efficiently and effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain audit-readiness processes and supporting documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support
